A MADALA died in a shack fire this morning in Katlehong, Ekurhuleni. Ekurhuleni emergency services spokesman, William Ntladi, told Daily Sun the old man was alone in a backyard shack at the time. “Residents saw a cloud of smoke and frantically tried to break in to save the old man from the fire,” said Ntladi. When firefighters arrived, residents were battling the blaze using water buckets,” said Ntladi. After the fire had been extinguished, the old man’s charred body was found under rubble. “Cops and all relevant stakeholders were called to the scene,” said Ntladi. The cause of the fire is under investigation.